  "description": "The event horizon is the boundary of a [black hole](./black-hole.md) -- the surface beyond which events cannot affect an outside observer. It is defined by the requirement that outgoing [light](../../../terms/light.md) rays at the horizon remain trapped: they can neither escape nor fall inward, but hover at the boundary forever.",
